Example:

Partition-0
|
|- Offset 0 -> A
|- Offset 1 -> B
|- Offset 2 -> C
|- Offset 3 -> D
|- Offset 4 -> E
|- Offset 5 -> F

Yahan Offset sirf message ki position batata hai.

Conceptually hum Partition ko offsets ke collection ke roop me dekhte hain jaha messages store kitye jaate hai.

Lekin internally Kafka Partition ko ek large append-only log file ki tarah treat karta hai.

Example:

Partition-0
|
|- Offset 0 -> A
|- Offset 1 -> B
|- Offset 2 -> C
|- Offset 3 -> D
|- Offset 4 -> E
|- Offset 5 -> F

Kafka ke perspective se ye poora structure (Partition-0) ek log file hai.

Agar time ke saath aur messages aate rahein:

Offset 6 -> G
Offset 7 -> H
Offset 8 -> I
...
Offset 10 Billion -> XYZ

To Partition ki underlying log file bahut badi ho sakti hai.

Example:

partition0.log

Ye file GBs ya TBs tak grow kar sakti hai, jise manage karna inefficient ho jata hai.

Is problem ko solve karne ke liye Kafka ek Partition ko internally multiple Log Segments me divide karta hai.

Example:

Partition-0
|
--Segment-1
|   |
|   |- Offset 0 -> A
