## PARTITION ASSIGNMENT STRATEGIES - CONSUMER GROUP KE ANDAR KAUNSI PARTITION KIS CONSUMER KO ASSIGN HOGI?
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Consumer Group ka Group Coordinator decide karta hai ki
Consumer Group ke kis Consumer ko kaunsi Partition assign hogi.

Ye decision ek Partition Assignment Strategy ke basis par liya jata hai.

Partition Assignment Strategy decide karti hai ki
Consumer Group ke available Consumers ke beech
Partitions ko kaise distribute kiya jayega.


## IMPORTANT
-------------

- Partition Assignment Strategies sirf Consumer Groups ke liye hoti hain.

- Standalone Consumers ke liye Kafka automatically decide nahi karta ki
  kaunsa Consumer kisi Topic ki kaunsi Partition consume karega.

- Standalone Consumers khud manually decide karte hain ki unhe kis
  Partition se read karna hai using the Consumer API (consumer.assign(...)).

- Ek Standalone Consumer chahe to sirf ek hi Partition consume kare
  ya multiple Partitions consume kare, ye decision Consumer khud leta hai.


## EXAMPLE :
-------------

Topic = Orders

Partitions:

Partition-0
Partition-1
Partition-2

Maan lo 3 Standalone Consumers hain jinhone Orders topic ko subscribe kiya hua hai :

Consumer-1
Consumer-2
Consumer-3

Consumer-1 agar sirf Partition-0 consume karna chahta hai:

consumer.assign(Arrays.asList(
    new TopicPartition("orders", 0)
));

Ya sirf Partition-1:

consumer.assign(Arrays.asList(
    new TopicPartition("orders", 1)
));

Ya saari Partitions:

consumer.assign(Arrays.asList(
    new TopicPartition("orders", 0),
    new TopicPartition("orders", 1),
    new TopicPartition("orders", 2)
));

Yaani Standalone Consumers khud manually Partitions assign karte hain.

Kafka is assignment me interfere nahi karta.


## PARTITION ASSIGNMENT STRATEGIES :
-------------------------------------

1. Range Assignor
2. Round Robin Assignor
3. Sticky Assignor
4. Cooperative Sticky Assignor

Maan lo Topic hai:

Orders

Aur isme 4 Partitions hain:

Orders
|
├── Partition-0
├── Partition-1
├── Partition-2
└── Partition-3


Ab maan lo 2 Consumers hain jo 'Orders' Topic ko subscribe kiye hue hain:

Consumer-1
Consumer-2

Aur ye dono same Consumer Group me hain:

Group = OrderProcessors


1. Range Assignor
-----------------

Assigns a continuous range of partitions to each consumer.

Assignment:

Consumer-1
|
Partition-0
Partition-1


Consumer-2
|
Partition-2
Partition-3


2. Round Robin Assignor
------------------------

Partitions ko consumers ke across relatively evenly distribute karta hai.

Assignment:

Consumer-1
|
Partition-0
Partition-2


Consumer-2
|
Partition-1
Partition-3


3. Sticky Assignor
------------------

Tries to keep the existing partition assignments unchanged
as much as possible to minimize partition movement during rebalancing.

Example:

Current Assignment:

Consumer-1
|
Partition-0
Partition-2

----------------

Consumer-2
|
Partition-1
Partition-3


Ab Consumer-3 join karta hai.

Isliye Rebalancing trigger hogi.

Agar Round Robin Assignor use ho,
to sabhi partitions dobara reassign honge.

Sticky Assignor jitna possible ho existing assignment ko preserve
karne ki koshish karta hai.

Suppose new assignment becomes:

Consumer-1
|
Partition-0


Consumer-2
|
|- Partition-1
|- Partition-3


Consumer-3
|
|- Partition-2


Yaani jitna kam partition movement ho sake utna.


## IMPORTANT :
---------------

Sticky Assignor Eager Rebalancing use karta hai.

Isliye final assignment me bhale hi sirf Partition-2 move ho,
lekin rebalance ke dauran pehle existing Consumers se
assigned Partitions temporarily revoke ki jaati hain.

Uske baad nayi assignment perform hoti hai.

Is wajah se rebalance ke dauran processing temporarily pause
ho sakti hai.


Benefits:

- Existing partition assignments ko maximum preserve karta hai.
- Unnecessary partition movement ko reduce karta hai.


4. Cooperative Sticky Assignor
-------------------------------

Ye Sticky Assignor ka improved version hai.

Unlike Sticky Assignor, Cooperative Sticky Assignor
Incremental Rebalancing use karta hai.

Isme sirf required Partitions hi revoke/move ki jaati hain.

Baaki Consumers apni existing Partitions par processing
continue rakhte hain.

Isliye processing interruption aur rebalance pause
kaafi kam ho jata hai.


## IMPORTANT
------------

Modern Kafka me generally:

partition.assignment.strategy

property use hoti hai.

Isme configure kar sakte ho:

- RangeAssignor
- RoundRobinAssignor
- StickyAssignor
- CooperativeStickyAssignor


