## LEADER REPLICA
------------------

Har partition ka ek leader hota hai.

Producer jo bhi message publish karta hai, agar wo message kisi particular partition me map hota hai, to sabse pehle us Partition ke Leader Replica me store hota hai.

Baaki copies/replica followers hoti hain.

Leader partion

   |

   +----> Follower partition

   |

   +----> Follower partition


## FOLLOWER REPLICA
---------------------

Follower partitions continuously leader partition se data copy karti rehta hai.

Consumer jab bhi kisi partition se data read karega, to wo hamesha us partition ke leader replica se hi data read karega.

Maan lo:

Broker-1 crash ho gaya.

Aur Broker-1 par:

Partition-0 (Leader) present tha.


Kafka detect karega ki Leader unavailable ho gaya hai.

Ab Kafka available Followers me se kisi ek ko promote kar dega.

Example:

Broker-3
 |
 Partition-0

Follower ---> Leader


- Ab going forward Producer aur Consumer dono naye Leader Replica se interact karenge.

- Agar koi naya message Partition-0 me map hota hai, to Producer us message ko Broker-3 par maujood Partition-0 ke Leader Replica me store karega.

- Similarly, Consumer bhi ab Partition-0 ka data Broker-3 par maujood naye Leader Replica se hi consume karega.


