## KAFKA WRITE REJECT KYU KAR RAHA HAI?
-------------------------------------------

Kafka essentially bol raha hai:

"Mere paas sufficient healthy replicas nahi hain. Main tumhe success nahi bol sakta."

Example:

min.insync.replicas = 2

Lekin currently ISR me sirf:

{Leader}

bacha hua hai.

Count = 1

Agar Kafka is situation me write accept kar le aur Producer ko ACK bhej de, to Producer maan lega ki data safely store ho gaya hai.

Lekin reality me message sirf Leader ke paas hai.

Ab agar ACK bhejne ke turant baad Leader bhi crash ho jaye, to us message ki koi synchronized copy available nahi hogi.

Result:

Data Loss

Isliye Kafka safety ko priority deta hai aur write reject kar deta hai.

IMPORTANT:
-----------

Write reject karne se Leader crash hone ki possibility khatam nahi hoti.

Leader phir bhi crash ho sakta hai.

Kafka ka logic hai:

"Jab tak mere paas required number of healthy replicas nahi hain, main write ki durability guarantee nahi kar sakta."

Isliye Kafka write reject karta hai.

In other words, Kafka write reject karke data loss ko impossible nahi banata, balki unsafe writes ko prevent karta hai aur durability guarantees ko maintain karta hai.


## MOST COMMON PRODUCTION CONFIGURATION
-----------------------------------------

Replication Factor = 3

acks = all

min.insync.replicas = 2

Ye configuration high durability aur fault tolerance provide karti hai.

Note : min.insync.replicas is enforced only when the producer uses acks=all.

