13 . Retention Policy
===============================================================================

After a consumer consumes the message from the topic that message is not deleted from the topic (technically partition's of the topic) , it stays there unlike other MQ like RabbitMQ
i.e
Partition-0

Offset 0 -> A
Offset 1 -> B
Offset 2 -> C
Offset 3 -> D

Consumer ne A,B,C,D read kar liya.

Partition me data fir bhi rahega.

Partition-0

Offset 0 -> A
Offset 1 -> B
Offset 2 -> C
Offset 3 -> D

Kuch delete nahi hua.

Fir Delete Kab Hota Hai?

Retention policy decide karti hai.

Kafka bolta hai:

Main data ko kitne time tak rakhunga before deleting? (Time based retention)

Ya

Main kitna storage limit tak data rakhunga before deleting? (Size Based Retention)

---------------------------------
KAFKA ME RETENTION SETTINGS:
----------------------------------

1. Broker Level (Global Default)
2. Topic Level (Override)


1: BROKER LEVEL RETENTION (Global Default)
--------------------------------------------

Agar kisi topic ne apni retention define nahi ki, to ye broker level retention use hogi. i.e Broker-level retention acts as the default for all topics
Note : Retention policy topic ke saare partitions par apply hoti hai, na ki kisi individual/particular partition par.

Kafka broker configuration me define kar sakte ho:

# Time based retention
  log.retention.hours=170

ya

# Size based retention
  log.retention.ms=604800000


## DEFAULT BROKER LEVEL RETENTION 
----------------------------------

Default Time-Based Retention:
log.retention.hours=168 (Matlab 7 days) 


Default size-Based Retention:
log.retention.bytes=-1 (Matlab: No size limit)

Size ki wajah se deletion nahi hogi.

Deletion sirf time-based retention ke basis par hogi.

Aur tumne: Topic level retention nahi di and Broker level retention bhi explicitily nahi di to Kafka broker ye default values use karta hai. 


## TRULY INFINITE RETENTION:
-----------------------------

Agar theoretically indefinitely retain karna ho to:

log.retention.ms=-1
log.retention.bytes=-1

Dono disable karne padenge.

Lekin production me almost kabhi nahi karte, warna disk bhar jayegi.


2: TOPIC LEVEL RETENTION (Most Common in Production)
--------------------------------------------------------

Topic-level configuration broker-level retention ko override kar deti hai.

Yaani agar tumne kisi specific topic par retention define ki hai, to us topic ke liye broker ki default retention settings use nahi hongi.

Suppose orders topic me sirf 1 partition hai.

Kafka internally partition ko multiple log segments me divide karke store karta hai.

Partition-0

Segment-1

Offset 0 -> A
Offset 1 -> B
Offset 2 -> C

Segment-2

Offset 3 -> D
Offset 4 -> E
Offset 5 -> F

Segment-3

Offset 6 -> G
Offset 7 -> H
Offset 8 -> I


1: TIME BASED RETENTION:
---------------------------

Example:

@Bean
public NewTopic ordersTopic() {

    return TopicBuilder.name("orders")
            .partitions(3)
            .replicas(3)
            .config(
                TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_CONFIG,
                TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_DELETE
            )
            .config(
                TopicConfig.RETENTION_MS_CONFIG,
                String.valueOf(7 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000) // 7 days
            )
            .build();
}

Explanation:

## TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_CONFIG
-------------------------------------

Purpose:

-> Kafka Topic ka cleanup behavior configure karne ke liye use hota hai.
-> Is property ke through hum Kafka ko batate hain ki purane records ka
   cleanup kaise karna hai.

Common Values:

1. TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_DELETE
2. TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_COMPACT


## TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_DELETE
-------------------------------------

Purpose:

-> Kafka ko batata hai ki cleanup ka method kya hoga.

Meaning:

-> Purana data delete karke cleanup karna hai.

Note:

-> Ye cleanup strategy hai.
-> Ye decide karta hai "cleanup kaise hoga".


## TopicConfig.RETENTION_MS_CONFIG
-------------------------------------

Purpose:

-> Kafka ko batata hai ki records kitne time tak retain karne hain.

Meaning:

-> Specified time complete hone ke baad purana eligible segments delete kiya ja sakta hai.

In This Example:

String.valueOf(7 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000)

-> 7 Days

Meaning:

-> Records ko 7 din tak retain karo.
-> 7 din ke baad eligible segments delete kiye ja sakte hain.

Note:
-> Ye cleanup strategy nahi hai.



In the above example:

Retention = 7 days

Kafka periodically check karta hai:

"Segment kitna purana hai?"

Current State:

Partition-0

Segment-1 (10 days old)

Offset 0 -> A
Offset 1 -> B
Offset 2 -> C

Segment-2 (5 days old)

Offset 3 -> D
Offset 4 -> E

Segment-3 (1 day old)

Offset 5 -> F
Offset 6 -> G

Ab Kafka dekhega:

Segment-1 = 10 days old

Retention = 7 days

To Kafka Segment-1 ko delete kar dega.

Result:

Partition-0

Segment-2

Offset 3 -> D
Offset 4 -> E

Segment-3

Offset 5 -> F
Offset 6 -> G


2: SIZE BASED RETENTION :
---------------------------

@Bean
public NewTopic ordersTopic() {

    return TopicBuilder.name("orders")
            .partitions(3)
            .replicas(3)
            .config(
                TopicConfig.RETENTION_BYTES_CONFIG,
                String.valueOf(10L * 1024 * 1024 * 1024) // 10 GB
            )
            .build();
}

In the above example:

Retention = 10 GB

Kafka periodically check karta hai:

"Total retained data kitna ho gaya hai?"

Current State:

Partition-0

Segment-1 (4 GB) (10 days old)

Offset 0 -> A
Offset 1 -> B
Offset 2 -> C

Segment-2 (5 GB) (5 days old)

Offset 3 -> D
Offset 4 -> E

Segment-3 (3 GB) (1 day old)

Offset 5 -> F
Offset 6 -> G

Total Retained Data:

4 GB + 5 GB + 3 GB = 12 GB

Ab Kafka dekhega:

Retention = 10 GB

Current Data = 12 GB

Limit exceed ho chuki hai.

Kafka oldest segment se cleanup start karega.

Is case me:

Segment-1 = 10 days old

To Kafka Segment-1 delete kar dega.

Result:

Partition-0

Segment-2 (5 GB)

Offset 3 -> D
Offset 4 -> E

Segment-3 (3 GB)

Offset 5 -> F
Offset 6 -> G


## IMPORTANT:
----------------

1: Consumer ne read kiya ya nahi kiya, koi farak nahi padta 
     Deletion sirf time / size ke basis par ho rahi hai.

2: Kafka har segment ke saath timestamp maintain karta hai.
   Generally segment ki age us time se calculate ki jaati hai jab segment create hua tha.

3: Kafka individual messages ya offsets ko delete nahi karta.
   Agar Kafka har message ko offset level par individually delete kare, to disk operations bahut expensive aur inefficient ho jayengi.
   Isliye Kafka segment-level deletion use karta hai, jo high-throughput systems ke liye kaafi efficient approach hai.

