14. LOG COMPACTION
===============================================================================

Retention ka Goal:
-> Storage bachana
-> Purana data delete karna

Compaction ka Goal:
-> Har key ki latest value bacha ke rakhna
-> Purani history corresponding to us key delete ho sakti hai


Log Compaction sirf tab useful hai jab messages ke paas KEY ho. Producer jab message publish karta hai to optionally ek KEY bhi pass kar sakta hai.

Ye KEY do kaam karti hai:

1. Partition decide karne me help karti hai
   partition = hash(key) % number_of_partitions

2. Compaction ke time Kafka isi KEY ka use karta hai ye identify karne ke liye
   ki kaunse records same entity ko represent karte hain.


ONE-LINE DEFINITION :
Log Compaction is a Kafka cleanup strategy that retains the latest record
for each key while allowing older records with the same key to be removed.


## EXAMPLE :
-------------

Maan lo ek Topic hai:

Topic = UserLocation

Aur Topic ke paas 2 Partitions hain:

Partition-0
Partition-1

Producer messages publish karta hai:

(Key=User1, Value=Delhi)

(Key=User1, Value=Mumbai)

(Key=User1, Value=Bangalore)

Meaning:

User1 pehle Delhi me tha
phir Mumbai shift hua
phir Bangalore shift hua


Kyuki teeno messages ki KEY same hai:

Key = User1

Isliye teeno messages same Partition me jayenge.

Suppose: Partition-0


Partition-0

Offset 0:
Key   = User1
Value = Delhi


Offset 1:
Key   = User1
Value = Mumbai

Offset 2:
Key   = User1
Value = Bangalore


## QUESTION :
-------------

Current City kya hai?

Answer: Bangalore


To Delhi aur Mumbai kyun rakhe hue hain?

Answer:

Historical tracking ke liye useful ho sakte hain.

Lekin kai systems ko history nahi chahiye.

Unhe sirf latest state chahiye.


## REAL WORLD EXAMPLE :
--------------------------

Topic:

CustomerPreferences

Messages:

(Key=User1, Value=Hindi)

(Key=User1, Value=English)

(Key=User1, Value=French)

Current Preference: French

Yahan Hindi aur English ki value ab business ke liye useful nahi hai.

Hume sirf latest state chahiye.


## COMPACTION ENABLE KARTE HAIN
---------------------------------

@Bean
public NewTopic userProfileTopic() {

return TopicBuilder.name("user-profile")
        .partitions(3)
        .replicas(3)
        .config(
            TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_CONFIG,
            TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_COMPACT
        )
        .build();
}


## TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_COMPACT
-------------------------------------

-> Log Compaction enable karta hai.
-> Har KEY ki latest value preserve karta hai.
-> Same KEY ke purane records eventually remove ho sakte hain.
-> Ye cleanup strategy hai.


------------------------------------
Kya Compaction instant hota hai ?
------------------------------------

Answer:

Compaction instant nahi hota.

Compaction ek background process hai. Kafka background me periodically cleanup run karta hai.

Kafka instant cleanup ki guarantee nahi deta.


Current State :

Partition-0

Offset 0:
Key   = User1
Value = Delhi


Offset 1:
Key   = User1
Value = Mumbai


Offset 2:
Key   = User1
Value = Bangalore


KAFKA KYA DEKHEGA?

Kafka observe karega: 

Key = User1

multiple baar aa rahi hai.

To Kafka latest record preserve karega.


AFTER COMPACTION :

Partition-0

Offset 2
Key   = User1
Value = Bangalore

Delhi aur Mumbai wale purane records eventually remove ho sakte hain.


------------------------------------
MOST IMPORTANT RULE
------------------------------------

Compaction works on: KEY

NOT VALUE

Kafka compare karta hai:

"Same Key?"

Agar same key hai:

Latest record preserve karo.

Purane records remove kiye ja sakte hain.


-------------------------------------
COMPACTION + RETENTION TOGETHER
-------------------------------------

Kafka me hum Retention aur Compaction dono ek saath use kar sakte hain.

## RETENTION & COMPACTION ENABLE KARTE HAIN:
-----------------------------------------------

##EXAMPLE:

@Bean
public NewTopic userProfileTopic() {

return TopicBuilder.name("user-profile")
        .partitions(3)
        .replicas(3)
        .config(
           TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_CONFIG,
           TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_COMPACT + "," + TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_DELETE
         )
        .config(
           TopicConfig.RETENTION_MS_CONFIG,
           String.valueOf(30L * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000) // 30 Days
         )
        .build();
}


Meaning:

##1. COMPACTION

   Same KEY ke multiple records hain:

   (User1, Delhi)

   (User1, Mumbai)

   (User1, Bangalore)

   To Kafka eventually latest value preserve karega:

   (User1, Bangalore)

   Purane records corresponding to the same KEY
   eventually remove kiye ja sakte hain.


##2. RETENTION

   Agar data retention policy violate karta hai
   (for example 30 days se purana ho jata hai),
   to Kafka segment level cleanup perform kar sakta hai.


