already execute ho chuke hain,

to Kafka unhe rollback nahi kar sakta.

Isliye non-Kafka operations ko safely handle karne ke liye
Business Idempotency, Saga Pattern ya Compensating Transactions
jaise application-level approaches ka use kiya jata hai.


===============================================================================
15. HIGH WATERMARK
===============================================================================

High Watermark ka purpose hai:

Consumer ko sirf wahi messages dikhana jo safely replicated
ho chuke hain, i.e. jo message jis partition ke Leader Replica
me store hua hai, wo us partition ke sabhi CURRENT ISR
(In-Sync Replicas) tak bhi successfully replicate ho chuka ho.

One Line Definition:

High Watermark is the highest offset of a partition that has been
successfully replicated to all CURRENT ISR replicas and is therefore
safe to expose to consumers.


## IMPORTANT:
--------------

High Watermark ka concept tab meaningful hota hai
jab replication enabled ho.

Agar:

Replication Factor = 1

matlab sirf ek hi replica (Leader Replica) exist karta hai,
to practically:

High Watermark = Leader Replica ka Last Offset

Kyunki synchronize karne ke liye koi follower replica
exist hi nahi karta.

Iska matlab:

Leader Replica me jo bhi messages successfully persist
ho jaate hain,

wo saare messages Consumer ko visible ho jaate hain.

Yaani Replication Factor = 1 ke case me,
High Watermark practically Leader ke Last Offset
ke barabar hota hai.

## IMPORTANT:
--------------

High Watermark partition ke sabhi replicas ko consider nahi karta.

High Watermark sirf partition ke CURRENT ISR
(In-Sync Replicas) ke basis par calculate hota hai,
na ki us partition ki total replicas ke basis par.


## Example:
-------------

Maan lo:

Topic = orders

Aur is topic ke paas sirf ek partition hai:

orders
   |
   +----> Partition-0

Aur:

Replication Factor = 3

Assume karo cluster me 3 brokers hain aur
Partition-0 ki replicas un brokers me distribute hain:

Broker-1 -> Leader
Broker-2 -> Follower-1
Broker-3 -> Follower-2

Maan lo Consumer-1 ne:

orders

topic ko subscribe kar rakha hai.

Producer ne 10 messages publish kiye aur
wo sabhi replicas tak successfully replicate ho gaye.

Current State:

Leader       Offset = 10
Follower-1   Offset = 10
Follower-2   Offset = 10

Current ISR:

ISR = {Leader, Follower-1, Follower-2}

Kyuki current ISR ke sabhi members
Offset 10 tak synchronized hain,

isliye:

High Watermark = 10


## NEW MESSAGE ARRIVES
-----------------------

Ab Producer ek aur message bhejta hai:

Offset 11 -> D

Ye message Leader Replica tak successfully
pahunch jata hai.

Lekin abhi followers tak replicate nahi hua.

Current State:

Leader Offset = 11
Follower-1 Offset = 10
Follower-2 Offset = 10

---------------------------------------------------------
## Question: Kya Consumer-1 ko message 'D' dikh jayega?
---------------------------------------------------------

Answer: NO.

Kyuki 'D' abhi tak saare CURRENT ISR replicas
tak replicate nahi hua hai.

Isliye:

High Watermark = 10

hi rahega.

Consumer sirf:

Offset <= High Watermark tak ke messages hi read kar sakta hai.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
## Question: WHY CAN A CONSUMER NEVER READ UNREPLICATED DATA FROM KAFKA? 
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Suppose Kafka 'D' ko Consumer-1 ko dikha deta.

Ab maan lo:

Leader crash (in Broker-1)

ho gaya.

New leader banega among the ISR members:
suppose Follower-1 -> Leader

Current State:

Leader       Offset = 10
Follower-2   Offset = 10


Message: 'D' gayab.

Ab consumer bol raha hai:

"Maine D read kar liya tha."

Kafka bol raha hai:

"Mere paas D hai hi nahi."

Ye impossible situation create ho jayegi.

Isliye Kafka rule banata hai:

Consumer ko kabhi bhi High Watermark
se aage ka data nahi dikhaya jayega.


## IMPORTANT
---------------

ISR ka matlab ye nahi hota:

Leader Offset == Follower Offset

exactly har microsecond.

Kafka followers ko thoda lag karne deta hai.

Example:

Leader      Offset = 100
Follower-1  Offset = 99
Follower-2  Offset = 99

Aur phir bhi:

ISR = {Leader, Follower-1, Follower-2}

ho sakta hai.

----------------
## AB MAAN LO:
----------------

Ab manlo ki follower-1 bhi data copy kar leta hai leader partition se but follower-2 piche reh jata hai  and Kafka use ISR se remove kar deta hai:

Old ISR:

    {Leader, Follower-1, Follower-2}

New ISR:

    {Leader, Follower-1}

Aur:

Leader       Offset = 11
Follower-1   Offset = 11

To:

    High Watermark = 11

ho jayega.

Ab Consumer ko:

    Offset 11 -> D

visible ho jayega.
